Sport and Recreation MEC Hlengiwe Mavimbela joined the South African Table Tennis Board to unveil the official logo for the 2023 International Tennis Federation Table Tennis (ITTF) Championship on Friday, 27 May. The championship will be held at the Durban ICC in May 2023. It will be one of the biggest and the first international table tennis event to ever been hosted in the country and will see table tennis fans and players from around the world participating. MEC Mavimbela said : “We were indeed excited on 28 September 2020, when the ITTF voted to award Durban the rights to host the 2023, which we all know is being hosted on the African continent for the first time since 1939 when these games were hosted in Egypt. We will be hosting this on behalf of the African continent.” Mavimbela also said that they will be hosting social cohesion programmes in different areas to mark the beginning of the legacy programme. “We are happy that after the unveiling of the logo, we will host the social cohesion programmes in different areas  for the ITTF World Table Tennis Championships Durban 2023. The availing of playing equipment, skills development and capacity building should be the cornerstone of the legacy project,” said MEC Mamvimbela.